        <item>
            <title>0.2.0</title>
            <description><![CDATA[
                <h2>Hide in full screen, rebuilt</h2>
                <p>The full-screen detection now asks macOS directly whether a full-screen Space is active, instead of guessing from window geometry. Contributed by <a href="https://github.com/hexxt-git">@hexxt-git</a>, with additional hardening on top.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Reliable on notched Macs; a maximized window no longer hides the island by mistake</li>
                    <li>Keeps working across Spaces (it previously could get pinned to one Space)</li>
                    <li>Tucks away <i>before</i> you switch to a full-screen app, so it no longer pops up over movies mid-switch</li>
                    <li>Still tucks right at the start of the full-screen transition</li>
                    <li>Crash-safe system calls and a fixture-tested parser under the hood</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Thanks to <b>hexxt-git</b> for the report and the fix.</p>
            ]]></description>
            <pubDate>Tue, 21 Jul 2026 12:21:47 +0200</pubDate>
            <sparkle:version>0.2.0</sparkle:version>
